<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by NightGod:
[B] For me, at least, recasting buffs to use as heals are still a MAJOR part of my healing strategy. Heroic bond is probably the best group heal I currently have, especially for AoE fights where everyone is dropping at pretty much the same, steady rate, plus it removes me having to keep up with that buff if I use at as a heal as well. And the next to nothing agro from it is a godsend. (Cast a group heal on a multi-mob pull and watch the agro /shudder). And Valor off my Donal's arms is awesome for small groups hunting faction/pharming (where the mobs are low enough to not present a major problem, but high enough to cause some damage) or for soloing (200HP mana free heal is amazing in the right situation). Most clerics in the 50s aren't going to have those smaller heals memmed-the space can be much better used by a stun or root to help with crowd control.
